.rss"/><img alt="" height="0" width="0" border="0" style="display:none" src="http://event.adxpose.com/event.flow?uid=38vYBtngNRREa1yL_Pixel&eventcode=000_000_12&location=&wh=&xy=&cid=Win7_ISV&duration=0&iframed=0&p=1"/>";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:38:"http://www.pheedo.com/namespace/pheedo";a:1:{s:8:"origLink";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:60:"http://blogs.sitepoint.com/2011/02/19/5-awesome-html5-games/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:32:"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/";a:1:{s:7:"creator";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:13:"Craig Buckler";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}}s:40:"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/";a:1:{s:7:"encoded";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:5474:"<p>It&#8217;s the end of the week and it&#8217;s been a while since I last looked at <a
href="http://blogs.sitepoint.com/2010/06/06/3-great-javascript-canvas-games-examples/">native browser-based games</a>. I&#8217;ve therefore picked a new selection for your <em>research</em> purposes &hellip; it&#8217;s amazing how far the technology has progressed within a few short months.</p><p>The following examples have all been implemented using HTML5 technologies such as <code>canvas</code> and JavaScript. They work in most modern browsers but most won&#8217;t work in Internet Explorer 8.0 and below. Chrome or Opera generally provide the best experience.</p><h2><a
href="http://playbiolab.com/">Biolab Disaster<img
src="http://blogs.sitepointstatic.com/images/tech/484-html5-canvas-games-biolab.png" width="300" height="225" alt="Biolab Disaster" class="imgright" style="border:1px solid #333" /></a></h2><p>While I&#8217;m far too young to remember 8-bit gaming in the 1980s, Biolab is a homage to those simpler but addictive titles from 20-30 years ago. The game is a space-themed platformer with colorful chunky sprites, great animation and sound effects. The developer, Dominic Szablewski, has also released the canvas-based library at <a
href="http://impactjs.com/">ImpactJS.com</a>.</p><p>Biolab is a fine game. In fact, it&#8217;s better than many released in the 80s &hellip; <em>so I&#8217;ve heard</em>.</p><h2><a
href="http://www.effectgames.com/effect/games/crystalgalaxy/">Crystal Galaxy<img
src="http://blogs.sitepointstatic.com/images/tech/484-html5-canvas-games-galaxy.jpg" width="300" height="225" alt="Crystal Galaxy" class="imgright" style="border:1px solid #333" /></a></h2><p>Crystal Galaxy is a sideways scrolling space shooter reminiscent of R-Type. However, the game&#8217;s unique in that the mouse controls the direction of the ship as well as its location.</p><p>Unusually, Crystal Galaxy doesn&#8217;t use the HTML5 canvas element. Every sprite is an individual HTML <code>div</code> moved around the screen. It works quickly in all browsers and is even playable in IE6! The authors at <a
href="http://www.effectgames.com/">EffectGames.com</a> also provide free tools and libraries to help you write your own titles.</p><p>Crystal Galaxy is fun and you won&#8217;t be able to resist another go.</p><h2><a
href="http://canvasrider.com/">Canvas Rider<img
src="http://blogs.sitepointstatic.com/images/tech/484-html5-canvas-games-rider.jpg" width="300" height="225" alt="Canvas Rider" class="imgright" style="border:1px solid #333" /></a></h2><p>As you might expect, Canvas Rider is a version of Line Rider implemented using the HTML5 canvas element. The game is simple: you ride a bicycle over a series of obstacles to reach a goal &#8212; but the realistic gravity and physics make it a serious challenge.</p><p>What makes Canvas Rider more special is the online track editor and the <a
href="http://canvasrider.com/tracks/561613">thousands</a> of <a
href="http://canvasrider.com/tracks/680331">tracks</a> <a
href="http://canvasrider.com/tracks/557438">submitted</a> by fans of the game.</p><h2><a
href="http://agent8ball.com/">Agent 008 Ball<img
src="http://blogs.sitepointstatic.com/images/tech/484-html5-canvas-games-008ball.jpg" width="300" height="225" alt="Agent 008 Ball" class="imgright" style="border:1px solid #333" /></a></h2><p>Agent 008 Ball is a glorious-looking game of pool for one player. The objective is to pot as many balls as possible before the timer runs out.</p><p>Again, Agent 008 Ball uses the HTML5 canvas element, but it&#8217;s the photo-realistic graphics and real-world physics make the game stand out.</p><h2><a
href="http://www.pirateslovedaisies.com/">Pirates Love Daisies<img
src="http://blogs.sitepointstatic.com/images/tech/484-html5-canvas-games-pirates.jpg" width="300" height="225" alt="Pirates Love Daisies" class="imgright" style="border:1px solid #333" /></a></h2><p>Pirate Love Daisies is a Tower-Defense-like game which pushes the boundaries of what&#8217;s possible with HTML5 and JavaScript. It was written by Flash developer Grant Skinner who was commissioned by Microsoft to create a game which showed off the new technologies in IE9.</p><p>The game works well in most browsers but, as you&#8217;d expect, it&#8217;s best on a fast PC using a browser with native hardware-accelerated graphics. For the moment, IE9 beta offers the best experience.</p><p>While a browser is never likely to be the best platform for games these titles show that a little ingenuity can yield amazing results. What&#8217;s your favorite and have you discovered any awesome HTML5 games?</p> <br clear="both" style="clear: both;"/>
